Four people have been allegedly shot dead and four others critically injured in an attack by unknown gunmen at a football field at Zunurug village, Kaura local government area of Kaduna State. The sad event, which affected mostly youths, occurred on Sunday around 6:30pm in the evening when the people were watching a football competition. An eyewitness, who sought anonymity, said the attackers came from a nearby bush and shot sporadically on the unsuspecting spectators, killing four on the spot. The witness said the development brought the football match to an end as the spectators ran for their dear lives. The source also disclosed that, in a nearby Tsonje village, on Sunday morning, the villagers woke up to discover the dead body of one of the residents, who died of gunshots. He said the victim identified as Dogara Kazzah was said to have gone to ease himself in the bush the previous night around 8pm but never returned. All efforts made to obtain reactions from the State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Yakubu Sabo was unsuccessful as of the time of filing this report. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.